@DarkOwl57 Uhhhh.... my cruiser is gone. Im just going to edit it back in, as it appears to have dissapeared from the save.

Edited April 19, 2017 by ShadowGoat

heres my turn. I killed the ares. It's basically useless. I removed all the g3s with a large explosion, as they were quite clearly ripped off of darkowls torpedos, and while it has engines left, it's basically dead. all it has are 6 i beams, and ive already moved my ship the heck out of there.

 

The Obliteration lining up the shot.

The torpedo making impact just after activating the cluster warhead

Carnage! Note: the pilot survived, as i dont want to kill any kerbals. The debris field was massive, though i didnt get a screenshot. Also i camoflauged my ship. Good luck finding it. Also just realized the old one dissapeared becuase i set it as debris to hide it. My technology is catching up. In a week i already have a one shot shipkiller.

Here's the persist. Your turn darkowl.

https://www.dropbox.com/s/zt5grhmw4ws47on/persistent.sfs?dl=0

18 minutes ago, ShadowGoat said:

i set it as debris to hide it.

You fool! Now they will know your secret!
Was that the ares that destroyed the Isles? if so, DANGIT I WANTED REVENGE MAN!

49 minutes ago, 0111narwhalz said:

You fool! Now they will know your secret!

No the secret is useless as I makes your ship disappear with the debris

Did you damage the Ares or the Apollo? Because that's a picture of a heavily damaged Apollo. 

Yes, original original one shot shipkiller missile... notice any similarities between them and my G4H?

And the apollo is not dead. It has engines and six I-Beams, which was enough to cut your carrier in half last battle. 

Quote

I removed all the g3s with a large explosion, as they were quite clearly ripped off of darkowls torpedos.

Come on! I have had my G3 Torpedoes for months! Darkowl literally admitted to getting them of the black market!

Oh wait.

Come on! I have had my G3 Torpedoes for months! Darkowl literally admitted to getting them of the black market! 

Just because they're off the black market- I mean..... From our... design.... facility- doesn't mean they're useless!

Also, don't expect the turn for a little bit; I've got a mountain of IRL stuffs to plow through

However, I checked in on the Isles Debris, and yeah. It's gone. How did you break my missiles?!?! There's at least 2 missiles with no I-beam and a couple without engines!

I removed all the g3s with a large explosion, as they were quite clearly ripped off of darkowls torpedos,

hahahahaha YES

(Final note) I had to admit, that was a TON of space debris around Minnimus. When I loaded in I was like "WELL THEN THIS IS INSANE" took like 10 minutes to find a target (The Helios (>:D) in the map view). I quicksaved, but as soon as I was preparing for the intersect, power outage dead. So that happened last night. Then I've got a school thing tonight at 6. *sigh* IRL REALLY doesn't want me to play this

3 hours ago, Joseph Kerman said:

If only I can join....

Oh wait.

 

Just watch and learn for now my friend. I made the mistake of going in guns blazing without doing my research. That's how we lost 2 brave crew. #RIP #NeverForget #WhyAmIUsingHashtags

Me too! I only have to move like 25m/s, but the maneuver node kept on wiggling about. I'm enlisting the help of a friend, who'll act as captain of the ship until I learn how to properly do this junk.
Make sure you are flying from the right control point. That really messed me up rendevousing during a friendly battle me and a friend did on the same computer.
Well the only POC (Point of control) is the cockpit. I mean that the maneuver node is just going insane when I get close to the end of the burn. Maybe a little break will let her get normalized again

couldn't you have been a bit more subtle? There was only ever 3 Ares.
Uhhhhhh...... plz don't?

Nice idea, but needs some MINOR improvements. Just checking, it's darkowls turn right now, right?

Edit: In other news, I just finished the EX-9 Eos Gen 2, which reworks the I-Beams. As opposed to the old, awkward stacked double I-Beam based rows, which features docking ports but actually clipped into the armour when released, the Gen 2 houses all the I-Beams in one compact custom shaped pod, which ejects automatically and is easily reloaded. It does all this while retaining the same relatively low 375 part count. I don't have any right now, but I will show pictures tomorrow.
